  "prompt": "How many times has Obama met Putin?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cut-off in October 2023, former U.S. President Barack Obama met with Russian President Vladimir Putin numerous times during his presidency. Some of the key meetings included:\n \n1. July 2009 in Moscow during Obama's first visit to Russia as President.\n2. June 2012 at the G20 summit in Mexico.\n3. September 2015 at the UN General Assembly in New York.\n4. Several meetings took place during larger international summits, such as the G20, G8, and NATO summits.\n\nThese interactions were marked by discussions on various critical issues such as arms reduction, Syrian conflict, Ukraine crisis, and election interference among others. Specific numbers and dates could vary, and for the most updated count and detailed circumstances of these meetings, you may want to refer to official records or reliable news sources.",
